"title": "5533: sleep, physical",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5533",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A gift from God providing necessary rest, usually at night, for the restoration of mind and body. It is sometimes denied, sometimes used by God for his purposes and sometimes abused by people.</p>\n<h2>Sleep is a gift from God</h2>\n<h3>It is pleasant and refreshing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:12\">ECC 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:5\">1KI 19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:26\">JER 31:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:12-John11:13\">JHN 11:12–11:13</a></p>\n<h3>It is God's gift to his faithful people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:2\">PSA 127:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:21-Prov3:24\">PRO 3:21–3:24</a></p>\n<h3>It is often denied to the wicked</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:22\">ISA 48:22</a></p>\n<h2>Sleep as a nocturnal activity</h2>\n<h3>It is associated with night-time</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:7\">1TH 5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:34\">LUK 17:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4\">JHN 9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:11-Rom13:12\">ROM 13:11–13:12</a></p>\n<h3>It is associated with dreams</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:11-Gen28:12\">GEN 28:11–28:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:1\">GEN 41:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:5\">GEN 41:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:7-Isa29:8\">ISA 29:7–29:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:1\">DAN 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:5\">DAN 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:1\">DAN 7:1</a></p>\n<h3>It is associated with sexual activity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:15-Gen30:16\">GEN 30:15–30:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:4</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:2\">GEN 16:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:4\">GEN 16:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:10\">GEN 26:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:3-Gen30:5\">GEN 30:3–30:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:22\">GEN 35:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:18\">GEN 38:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:14\">GEN 39:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:16\">EXO 22:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:22\">DEU 22:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:7\">2SA 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a></p>\n<h2>Blessings in sleep</h2>\n<h3>Peace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:8\">PSA 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:24\">MAT 8:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:38\">MRK 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:23\">LUK 8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:6\">ACT 12:6</a></p>\n<h3>Protection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:3-Ps121:4\">PSA 121:3–121:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:5-Ps3:6\">PSA 3:5–3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:13\">PSA 68:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:25\">EZK 34:25</a></p>\n<h2>Deep and light sleep</h2>\n<h3>Deep sleep for the creation of Eve</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:21\">GEN 2:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Deep sleep for revelation</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:12\">GEN 15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:12-Job4:13\">JOB 4:12–4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:14-Job33:18\">JOB 33:14–33:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:2\">DAN 7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13\">DAN 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:9\">ACT 16:9</a></p>\n<h3>Deep sleep as a judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:12\">1SA 26:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:10\">ISA 29:10</a> <em>The sleep in this instance is symbolic.</em></p>\n<h3>Light sleep</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:2\">SNG 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Sleeping at the wrong time</h2>\n<h3>While on duty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:15\">PRO 19:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:13\">MAT 28:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:36\">MRK 13:36</a></p>\n<h3>During harvest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:5\">PRO 10:5</a></p>\n<h3>Instead of praying</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:5-Jonah1:6\">JON 1:5–1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:40\">MAT 26:40</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:37\">MRK 14:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:45-Luke22:46\">LUK 22:45–22:46</a></p>\n<h3>During a sermon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:9\">ACT 20:9</a></p>\n<h3>At the transfiguration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:32\">LUK 9:32</a></p>\n<h3>Amidst danger</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:13-Judg16:14\">JDG 16:13–16:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:19\">JDG 16:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:1-Prov6:5\">PRO 6:1–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:34\">PRO 23:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:25\">MAT 13:25</a></p>\n<h2>Excessive sleep</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:9-Prov6:11\">PRO 6:9–6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:13\">PRO 20:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:21\">PRO 23:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:10\">ISA 56:10</a></p>",
